## Step 1: Create Your AWS Account
1. Go to aws.amazon.com
2. Click "Create an AWS Account"
3. Enter your email and password
4. Provide contact information
5. Add payment method (credit card)
6. Verify your phone number
7. Choose support plan (Basic - Free)

## Step 2: Understand the AWS Console
- **Dashboard**: Main page with service overview
- **Services menu**: Access all AWS services
- **Region selector**: Choose your location (recommend us-east-1 for beginners)
- **Account menu**: Billing, security, support
- **Search bar**: Quick access to services and documentation

**Recommended regions for beginners**: us-east-1 (N. Virginia) or us-west-2 (Oregon)
**Documentation**: [AWS Console User Guide](https://docs.aws.amazon.com/awsconsolehelpdocs/)

## Step 3: Set Up Security (Very Important!)
### Enable MFA (Multi-Factor Authentication)
1. Go to IAM service
2. Click on your username
3. Security credentials tab
4. Assign MFA device
5. Use Google Authenticator app

### Create IAM User (Don't use root account)
1. Go to IAM â†’ Users
2. Click "Add user"
3. Enter username
4. Select access type
5. Attach policies
6. Download credentials

## Step 4: Launch Your First EC2 Instance
1. Go to EC2 service
2. Click "Launch Instance"
3. Choose Amazon Linux 2 AMI
4. Select t2.micro (free tier)
5. Configure security group (allow SSH port 22)
6. Create key pair (download .pem file)
7. Launch instance

**Cost**: Free (750 hours/month for 12 months)
**Documentation**: [EC2 Getting Started](https://docs.aws.amazon.com/ec2/)

### Troubleshooting:
- **Can't connect**: Check security group allows SSH (port 22)
- **Key pair issues**: Ensure .pem file permissions are 400 (chmod 400 keyname.pem)
- **Instance won't start**: Check if you've exceeded free tier limits

## Step 5: Create S3 Bucket (Simple Storage Service)
1. Go to S3 service
2. Click "Create bucket"
3. Enter unique bucket name (globally unique)
4. Choose region (same as EC2 for lower latency)
5. Keep default settings
6. Create bucket
7. Upload a test file

**Cost**: Free (5GB storage, 20,000 GET requests, 2,000 PUT requests/month)
**Documentation**: [S3 Getting Started](https://docs.aws.amazon.com/s3/)

### Troubleshooting:
- **Bucket name taken**: Try adding numbers or your initials
- **Access denied**: Check bucket policies and IAM permissions
- **Upload fails**: Verify file size limits and internet connection

## Step 6: Monitor Your Usage
### Check Free Tier Usage
1. Go to Billing Dashboard
2. Click "Free Tier"
3. Monitor usage limits
4. Set up billing alerts

### Set Up Billing Alerts
1. Go to CloudWatch
2. Create alarm
3. Set threshold ($5-10)
4. Add email notification

## Step 7: Set Up AWS CLI (Optional but Recommended)
1. Download AWS CLI from aws.amazon.com/cli/
2. Install on your computer
3. Run `aws configure`
4. Enter Access Key ID and Secret Access Key
5. Set default region and output format
6. Test with `aws s3 ls`

**Documentation**: [AWS CLI User Guide](https://docs.aws.amazon.com/cli/)

## Step 8: Learn with Hands-On Labs
### Recommended Learning Path:
1. **Week 1**: EC2 and S3 basics
   - Launch instances, connect via SSH
   - Create buckets, upload/download files
   - **Practice project**: Host a static website on S3
